<!-- PROBLEM / SOLUTION BRIDGE -->
<div class="pvh-problem-section">
  <div class="pvh-problem-inner">
    <div class="pvh-problem-col">
      <span class="pvh-section-tag" style="color:#7DCEA0;">The hidden problem</span>
      <h2 class="pvh-problem-heading">Cats weren't built to drink from bowls.</h2>
      <p class="pvh-problem-body">They descend from desert ancestors who got their water from running streams — never standing pools. Stagnant water in a bowl looks suspicious to their senses, so most cats drink just enough to survive, not enough to thrive. The result is chronic mild dehydration, urinary problems, and kidney stress that builds up silently over years.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="pvh-problem-col">
      <span class="pvh-section-tag" style="color:#7DCEA0;">The fix</span>
      <h2 class="pvh-problem-heading">Brook gives them the running water they actually want.</h2>
      <p class="pvh-problem-body">A constant gentle stream of filtered, oxygenated water — quiet enough that cats come back to it on their own. Most owners notice their cat drinking from it within the first day. More water in, more health out.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

